[cdp] Add the ability to listen for page mutations

Note, this is a pretty rubbish implementation, and needs to be made
more robust, but it suffices to show that the idea works.
[cdp] Add callbacks for console log events
[cdp] Throw an exception if unable to process a message
[cdp] Allow the chromium driver to register for event callbacks

[cdp] Fixes in the client generator

Notably:

 * `any` type maps to `java.lang.Object` and not a `Map`
 * Use default values that map to primitive types (`false` for
   booleans, `0` for numbers, `null` in other cases)

commit.message: Adding prebuilts for IE driver content-length header change
Add missing copyright header
[cdp] Add a fallback no-op version of CDP
[cdp] Look up CDP implementation dynamically

[cdp] Implement an idealized CDP protocol over v84 of CDP

We isolate Selenium from the fact that the CDP changes frequently by
presenting our own API to use (the `idealized` package) and
implementing that separately for each version of the protocol we
use. It's not elegant, but it works.

This change modifies that idealized CDP and makes it work with v84 of
the existing CDP, proving out that the changes work.
[bazel] Not all browser tests are also remote
Bump OpenTelemetry to 0.7.1

Remove `OPTIONS` from `HttpMethod`

The underlying functionality is handled by the Netty server, so our
servers should never see this requests. Tested locally by firing up
the standalone server and using GraphiQL to poke the `/graphql`
endpoint.
